concept_explanation.node_and_list:
**Linked List Node — the building block:**

```java
// Singly linked:
class ListNode {
    int val;
    ListNode next;
    ListNode(int val) { this.val = val; }
    ListNode(int val, ListNode next) { this.val = val; this.next = next; }
}

// Build list 1→2→3→null:
ListNode head = new ListNode(1, new ListNode(2, new ListNode(3)));

// Traversal: O(n)
ListNode curr = head;
while (curr != null) {
    System.out.print(curr.val + " ");
    curr = curr.next;
}

// Dummy head pattern — eliminates edge cases:
ListNode dummy = new ListNode(0);
dummy.next = head; // dummy → actual head
// Operations work uniformly — prev is never null
```

